== Merchandise ==
A series of collections called "The Bad Girls Club collection", which began in 2008 with the start of [[The Bad Girls Club (season 3)|season 3]], is an [[Online shopping|online boutique]] that fans of the show can order via [[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]]'s website, ''Shopoholic.com''. Oxygen has released a series of [[Trousers|pants]], [[shirts]] and [[sweaters]], mostly decor of the ''Bad Girls Club'' logo attached. The series of [[jewellery]], [[List of food preparation utensils|kitchen utensils]], [[Summer clothing|beach wear]], [[pillows]], [[blanket]]s, and [[Panties|women underwear]] also includes the ''Bad Girls Club'' logo design. The store, mostly women accessories, also has a line of [[Boxer shorts|boxers]] for men<ref name="shopoholic">{{cite web |url=http://www.shopoholic.com/eSource/PK/ecom/eSource/items/items-2-S1-lV1BadGirlsCl-lV2OXY.aspx?store=OXYv3 |title=Shopoholic - Bad Girls Club collection |author= |date= |work= |publisher=[[Oxygen.com]] |accessdate=6 February 2011}}</ref>

== Controversies ==
=== Season 4 ===
During the premier episode of [[The Bad Girls Club (season 4)|season 4]], ''[[List of The Bad Girls Club episodes (season 4)|Off The Wall]]'', [[Natalie Nunn]] and Annie Andersen began talking about which [[night clubs]] they should attend. When Natalie asked if Annie liked [[Chris Brown]]{{dn}}, Annie replied "No! - he beat up his girlfriend". Natalie then went on the defense for Brown stating that "Who cares, [[Rihanna]] [she] was a punk bitch, and she got her ass whop for a reason". Natalie then began saying that Rihanna is a crazy "bitch" and told Annie that she doesn't know her, like Natalie does, after Annie told Natalie that she doesn't agree with [[domestic violence]]. When the episode aired, Chris Brown reportedly stated that he doesn't know who Natalie Nunn was, which was questioned by Natalie during the reunion show.<ref name="bossip">{{cite web |url=http://bossip.com/173887/bossip-exclusive-natalie-nunn-says-chris-brown-is-lying-we-chopped-it-up-and-he-chopped-it-down/ |title=*Bossip Exclusive* Natalie Nunn says Chris Brown is Lying<U+2026> We Chopped it Up and He Chopped it Down!!! |author=Bossip Staff |date=31 October 2009 |work= |publisher=[[Bossip]] |accessdate=6 February 2011}}</ref> Natalie then stated that Brown made that comment, because the cast of the show wasn't unveiled yet. [[Perez Hilton]] then asked Natalie if Rihanna had confronted her after her comment that she had made towards Rihanna. Natalie then answered yes, stating that the two had reportedly been arguing during a dinner party in [[New York City]].<ref name="ep15">{{Cite episode |title=Episode 15 "Reunion Part I: Breaking Point" Season 4 |episodelink= |url= |accessdate= |series=15 |serieslink= |credits= |network=[[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]] |station= |city=[[Los Angeles]] |airdate=16 March 2010 |began= |ended= |season=4 |seriesno=415 |number= |minutes=60}}</ref> During the reunion, Natalie began stating rumors that she and Chris Brown had a fling prior to the show.<ref name="ep1">{{Cite episode |title=Episode 1 "Off The Wall" Season 4 |episodelink= |url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/Bad-Girls-2009/episode-1-season-4/wall/284911 |accessdate=30 November 2009 |series=1 |serieslink= |credits= |network=[[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]] |station= |city=[[Los Angeles]] |airdate=1 December 2009 |began= |ended= |season=4 |seriesno=401 |number= |minutes=60}}</ref><ref name="ep16">{{Cite episode |title=Episode 16 "Reunion Part II: It Ain't Over" Season 4 |episodelink= |url= |accessdate= |series=16 |serieslink= |credits= |network=[[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]] |station= |city=[[Los Angeles]] |airdate=23 March 2010 |began= |ended= |season=4 |seriesno=416 |number= |minutes=60}}</ref> Shortly before season 4's reunion was over, Natalie Nunn expressed that she doesn't condone domestic violence and apologized if her comment had enraged fans and other people who had gone through domestic violence.<ref name="ep16"/>

During the episode "Bad Break", Amber McWha began questioning, while drunk, homosexuality and the [[Bible]] and contrasting the two about the [[Christianity and homosexuality|christian]] faith towards [[Adam and Eve]]. This outraged [[Florina "Flo" Kaja]] to question Amber's [[homophobia]] while stating that she had made out with other women. The two began battling out their words, until Amber McWha pushed Flo into the pool, damaging her [[ankles]]. Under tremendous pain, Flo gets out of the pool and grabs Amber's hair and throws her across the [[Concrete|concrete.]]<ref name="rx">{{cite web |url=http://www.hiphoprx.com/2010/01/20/bad-girls-club-4-amber-and-flo-crazy-fight-over-lesbian-gay-affairs-photos/ |title=Bad Girls Club 4: Amber and Flo Crazy Fight Over Lesbian, Gay Affairs (Photos) |author=J.R. |date=20 January 2010 |work= |publisher=HipHopRX.com |accessdate=6 February 2011}}</ref><ref name="ep7recap">{{cite web |url=http://www.realitytea.com/2010/01/19/bad-girls-club-episode-7-recap-flo-gets-a-second-chance/ |title=Bad Girls Club Episode 7 Recap: Flo Gets A Second Chance |author= |date=19 January 2010 |work= |publisher=RealityTea.com |accessdate=6 February 2011}}</ref>

=== Season 5 ===
During the episode "[[List of The Bad Girls Club episodes (season 5)|The Wicked Witch Of Key West]]", Kristen Kelly was at a bar with Christina Marie Hopkins. While there, a random guy offered to buy drinks for the two ladies. While doing so, the guy added [[Phencyclidine|PCP]] [[hypnotic]] sleeping pills which made Kristen to be [[Toxication|intoxicated]]. Kristen claimed she suffered bruises on her body when the guy grabbed her and handled her roughly. Kristen also reported that the producers of the show didn't want to air the guy on television in order to not be sued.<ref name="PH">{{cite web |url=http://perezhilton.com/2010-11-17-kristen-claims-she-was-drugged-in-fight-with-lea |title=Bad Girl Kristen Claims She Was Drugged During Fight With Lea |author=[[Perez Hilton]] |date=17 November 2010 |work= |publisher=[[PerezHilton.com]] |accessdate=6 February 2011}}</ref>

