== Spin-offs ==
=== ''Bad Girls Road Trip'' ===
{{main|Bad Girls Road Trip}}
''Bad Girls Road Trip'' is a spin-off from Oxygen's original show, ''The Bad Girls Club.'' It premiered June 21, 2007. It starred season one veterans, Zara Sprankle, Aimee Landi, and Leslie Ramsue, who tour their respective hometowns, searching for casting opportunities for [[The Bad Girls Club (season 2)|Season 2]] of ''The Bad Girls Club.'' While on their roadtrip they also visited their former housemates.<ref name="roadtrip">{{cite web |url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1001468/ |title=Bad Girls Road Trip |author= |date= |work= |publisher=[[Internet Movie Database]] |accessdate=6 February 2011}}</ref>

=== ''Love Games: Bad Girls Need Love Too'' ===
{{main|Love Games: Bad Girls Need Love Too}}
''Love Games: Bad Girls Need Love Too'' premiered on March 16, 2010 and features three former ''Bad Girls Club'' stars; Amber Meade, Sarah Michaels (both from [[The Bad Girls Club (season 3)|Season 3]]) and Kendra Jones ([[The Bad Girls Club (season 4)|Season 4]]) "trying to find the man of their dreams" from a selection of 13 eligible bachelors. Comedian [[Bret Ernst]] hosted the [[Love Games: Bad Girls Need Love Too (season 1)|first season]], which consisted of eight one-hour [[List of Love Games: Bad Girls Need Love Too episodes (season 1)|episodes]] with [[Tanisha Thomas]] and Tiffany Torrence-Davis as guest stars in one episode. Oxygen networks have renewed the show for its [[Love Games: Bad Girls Need Love Too (season 2)|second season]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/01/10/oxygen-plays-matchmaker-with-love-games-bad-girls-need-love-too-in-march-2010/38294 |title=Oxygen Plays Matchmaker With <U+201C>Love Games: Bad Girls Need Love Too<U+201D> In March 2010 | publisher=TVbytheNumbers.com | work=[[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]] | date=January 10, 2010 | accessdate= January 11, 2010}}</ref> It was confirmed that Tanisha Thomas would become the host of season two, replacing Ernst. [[Natalie Nunn]] (Season 4), Amber Buhl (Season 3) and Lea Beaulieu (Season 5) will compete in season two, which will air on [[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]] in April of 2011.<ref name="lg">{{cite web |url=http://love-games.oxygen.com/lovegames/photos/meet-the-cast-season-2 |title=Meet the Cast: Season 2 |author= |date= |work= |publisher=[[Oxygen.com]] |accessdate=6 February 2011}}</ref>
Follow on Twitter @jaloof_anon_101 (Disguise Page)
=== ''Bad Girls Club: Flo Gets Married'' ===
''Bad Girls Club: Flo Gets Married'' is an upcoming one-hour special that centers around season four fan favorite [[Florina "Flo" Kaja]]'s marriage at a traditional [[Albanians|Albanian]] wedding and pregnancy. It will air on Oxygen on February 28, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2011/02/09/oxygen-medias-bad-girl-is-entering-uncharted-territory-in-bad-girls-club-flo-gets-married-on-february-28-at-9-pm-et-pt-383504/20110209oxygen01/|title=Oxygen Media's "Bad Girl" Is Entering Uncharted Territory in "Bad Girls Club: Flo Gets Married" on February 28 at 9 PM ET/PT|publisher=The Futon Critic|date=February 9, 2011|accessdate=February 11, 2011}}</ref>

== Other media ==
=== Mobile games ===
In 2007, Oxygen released a [[3G]] mobile game based on ''The Bad Girls Club'' in partnership with [[Artificial Life, Inc]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.multichannel.com/article/CA6462175.html|author=Reynolds, Mike|title=Oxygen Announces Mobile Game, Local-Ad-Sales Promo|publisher=Multichannel News|date=July 23, 2007}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.softpedia.com/news/The-Bad-Girls-Club-3G-Make-Sexy-Mobile-Game-61232.shtml|author=Balan, Elena|title=The Bad Girls Club 3G Makes Sexy Mobile Game|publisher=[[Softpedia]]|date=July 27, 2007}}</ref>  The 3G game featured 3D [[Avatar (computing)|avatar]]s based on the Bad Girls, as well as photo-realistic locations based on the actual house.

